description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/meshcore/adapter.c
Line: 386-389

The code only pops the pending event when enqueue() returns exactly 0:
```c
ret = enqueue(adapter, out, (size_t)ret);
if (ret == 0) {
    pending_pop(adapter);
}
```

If the enqueue_tx callback returns a positive value to indicate success (e.g., number of bytes enqueued), the pending event is never popped. This causes the same event to be re-delivered on the next SYNC_NEXT_MESSAGE command, leading to duplicate message delivery.

Fix: Change condition to `if (ret >= 0)` to handle both success conventions.
